{{define "content"}}
    {{/* Breadcrumb */}}
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumbs" class="crumb">
        <a href="/admin">Admin</a>
        <span class="crumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <a href="/admin/quizzes">Quizzes</a>
        <span class="crumb-sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span class="text-text" aria-current="page">Import</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-end md:justify-between gap-6 mb-10 pb-6 border-b border-border-soft">
        <div>
            <h1 class="m-0 font-display font-extrabold leading-none uppercase tracking-tight text-[clamp(2rem,6vw,2.75rem)]">{{.Title}}</h1>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-[60ch] text-text-dim text-[0.95rem]">
                Paste a JSON document into the textarea to create a quiz in one shot. Two steps:
            </p>
            <ol class="mt-3 max-w-[60ch] list-decimal pl-5 text-text-dim text-[0.95rem] space-y-1">
                <li>Copy the prompt + example below into an LLM chat. Edit the prompt to describe the quiz you want.</li>
                <li>Paste the chat's JSON reply into the textarea below and submit.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </header>

    {{if .Error}}
        <div class="mb-6 px-4 py-3 rounded-sm bg-danger/10 border border-danger/40 text-danger text-[0.9rem]" role="alert">
            {{.Error}}
        </div>
    {{end}}

    <form class="form-shell" action="/admin/quizzes/import" method="POST">
        <input type="hidden" name="csrf_token" value="{{csrfToken}}">

        <div class="form-field">
            <label class="label-eyebrow" for="json">
                Quiz JSON
                <span class="label-hint">UTF-8, no comments, unknown fields are rejected</span>
            </label>
            <textarea id="json" name="json" rows="18" spellcheck="false"
                      placeholder="Paste your quiz JSON here..."
                      class="form-input min-h-[360px] resize-y font-mono text-[0.85rem]">{{.JSON}}</textarea>
        </div>

        <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Import quiz</button>
            <a href="/admin/quizzes" class="btn-ghost">Cancel</a>
        </div>
    </form>

    <section aria-label="LLM prompt" class="form-shell mt-12">
        <h2 class="label-eyebrow mb-3 text-text">Prompt to paste</h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-text-dim text-[0.9rem]">
            Copy the block below into a chat. Replace the topic sentence at the bottom with the quiz you want.
        </p>
        <pre class="overflow-auto p-4 rounded-sm bg-surface border border-border-soft font-mono text-[0.78rem] leading-[1.5] text-text-dim"><code>Generate a quiz as a single JSON document matching this exact shape. Output only the JSON - no commentary, no code fences, no comments. Unknown fields are rejected.

Fields:
- title (string, required)
- description (string, required)
- timeLimitSeconds (integer, optional) - default answer window in seconds; per-question override below wins
- rounds (array, in play order, required) - each named round has:
    - title (string, required)
    - summary (string, optional) - shown to the player between rounds
    - questions (array, in play order, required) - each has:
        - text (string, required)
        - options (array of {text, correct}, required)
        - timeLimitSeconds (integer, optional) - overrides the quiz default for this question

Example shape:

{{.Example}}

Generate a quiz about: [REPLACE WITH YOUR TOPIC]</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section aria-label="Field reference" class="form-shell mt-12">
        <h2 class="label-eyebrow mb-3 text-text">Field reference</h2>
        <ul class="text-text-dim text-[0.9rem] space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">title</code> - string, required. Slug is derived server-side.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">description</code> - string, required.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">timeLimitSeconds</code> - integer, optional. Quiz-wide default answer window.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">rounds[].title</code> - string, required. Names the round.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">rounds[].summary</code> - string, optional. Shown to the player between rounds.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">rounds[].questions[].text</code> - string, required.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">rounds[].questions[].timeLimitSeconds</code> - integer, optional. Overrides the quiz default.</li>
            <li><code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">rounds[].questions[].options[]</code> - array of <code class="font-mono text-[0.8rem]">{text, correct}</code>. At least one option must be correct.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
{{end}}
